gomodel:SYNGO_263  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Flotillin-2 is found in synaptic proteomes (in detergent-resistant membranes associated to postsynaptic density preparations). It seems to be present in both pre- (SynGO-ID 260) and postsynaptically.. Experimental description: Wistar rats (6-week-old males) were killed by decapitation and forebrains were dissected and stored at -80 °C until use (p. 65)." ;
